00:11:59,799 --> 00:12:01,600
Well, there's lots of trees.

265
00:12:01,600 --> 00:12:03,600
So are you going for a big tree, a little tree?

266
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:06,000
What kind of tree are you going for here?

267
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:10,399
I'm going to go for a medium plus size of tree.

268
00:12:10,399 --> 00:12:11,000
All right.

269
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:12,200
All right.

270
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:13,800
Give me give me a strength check

271
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:16,800
to see how quickly you take down this piece of...

272
00:12:16,800 --> 00:12:18,200
That is a 21.

273
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:20,200
Best rolls we've ever had.

274
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:22,000
We're fucking catching dinner

275
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:25,000
and chopping down firewood.

276
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:26,200
It takes you a couple of swings,

277
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:29,000
but yeah, you fell this tree

278
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:32,000
and chop up what you need there

279
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:36,600
and bring it back to the fire

280
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:44,800
where Thea and Thaddeus are just sitting, waiting.

281
00:12:44,800 --> 00:12:45,800
He hops up and he says,

282
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:48,000
oh, good, the firewood.

283
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,399
I'll get started on the fire.

284
00:12:49,399 --> 00:12:51,200
So Thaddeus goes and starts up the fire.

285
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:52,399
Are we all back here now?

286
00:12:52,399 --> 00:12:54,800
Yeah, everybody's back.

287
00:12:54,800 --> 00:12:57,600
I look at New Laura and I go,

288
00:12:57,600 --> 00:13:00,800
only one rabbit has a munchies.

289
00:13:04,399 --> 00:13:05,200
You'll be fine.

290
00:13:05,200 --> 00:13:08,200
We have lots of other supplies from the airship.

291
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:09,200
Fair enough, fair enough.

292
00:13:09,200 --> 00:13:12,000
I pass her a bag of Cheezys.

293
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,400
That's what rations means.

294
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:15,400
I get that.

295
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:17,200
Cheesy poofs.

296
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:18,000
I look at them and go,

297
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:20,000
I wish they were Cheetos.

298
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:22,200
So yeah, Thaddeus goes and he starts the fire

299
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:24,800
and everything gets cooking there.

300
00:13:24,800 --> 00:13:28,000
So wait, Thaddeus started the fire?

301
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:28,600
I don't know.

302
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:30,800
He hopped up because he was tired of sitting

303
00:13:30,800 --> 00:13:32,000
in awkward silence with Thea

304
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:33,800
and came over and grabbed some wood for a meal.

305
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:36,400
Well, we didn't start the fire.

306
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:39,600
But was it always burning since the world was turning?

307
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:43,200
Thank you, Amy.

308
00:13:43,200 --> 00:13:44,000
Thank you for fighting along with me.

309
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:44,600
You're welcome.

310
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:46,000
I totally caught on.

311
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:47,200
Wait, Thaddeus started.

312
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:50,000
I was like, well, we didn't start the fire.

313
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:55,000
And he is...

314
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:57,800
Just moving along.

315
00:13:57,800 --> 00:14:00,800
Everybody's sitting around and Thaddeus pipes up

316
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:04,800
and he says, so...

317
00:14:04,800 --> 00:14:07,600
How long have you guys been around with Grancis?

318
00:14:07,600 --> 00:14:10,000
It seems like forever.

319
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:12,800
You know, Grancis is one of those guys.

320
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:15,400
It just it doesn't matter how long you're with him.

321
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:18,800
It just seems like eternity.

322
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:20,400
And then God rests his soul.

323
00:14:20,400 --> 00:14:23,800
Then it's gone all too fast, isn't it?

324
00:14:23,800 --> 00:14:25,800
Yeah, a little bit.

325
00:14:25,800 --> 00:14:27,400
Thea gets a little nostalgic.

326
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:30,600
She's like, remember that time?

327
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:33,200
He served us mashed potatoes and we all shrunk.

328
00:14:33,200 --> 00:14:35,000
Oh, I do remember that.

329
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:36,600
Boy, do I.

330
00:14:36,600 --> 00:14:39,200
What a fun adventure that was.

331
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:48,200
Yeah, he had a knack for messing up spells, didn't he?

332
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:50,800
Well, sure saved our ass at the end.

333
00:14:50,800 --> 00:14:52,000
Yeah, he did.

334
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:55,000
And the airship came in really handy a lot of times.

335
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:56,000
He was a good guy.

336
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:57,600
We weren't with him too long.

337
00:14:57,800 --> 00:15:03,000
And even in the time we knew him, we didn't spend a lot of time with him.

338
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:06,800
He kind of just picked us up and shuttled us around.

339
00:15:06,800 --> 00:15:16,200
And that's mostly it, except for that whole mashed potato grung thing.

340
00:15:16,200 --> 00:15:20,200
Well, I spent some more time with Grancis.

341
00:15:20,200 --> 00:15:23,800
We had a bit of a falling out.

342
00:15:23,800 --> 00:15:34,000
But yeah, we traveled a lot back, well, when I was more your ages of sorts.

343
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:42,400
We had a team of adventurers, you could say, who went on missions not unlike yourself.

344
00:15:42,400 --> 00:15:46,000
Not quite to the scale that you guys are doing here with the world saving.

345
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:55,799
But I remember a time we were in the thick of a large battle with some goblins.

346
00:15:55,799 --> 00:16:02,399
We were supposed to go stop this tribe of goblins from wrecking this little civilization,

347
00:16:02,399 --> 00:16:06,200
this little settlement that was having problems with them.

348
00:16:06,200 --> 00:16:10,200
It was supposed to be an easy in-for-some-out job, that sort of thing.

349
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:15,600
But their colony was much bigger than what we had been led on.

350
00:16:15,600 --> 00:16:21,600
We found ourselves with our backs against the wall, and then out of nowhere,

351
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:25,399
Grancis remembers that he can polymorph things.

352
00:16:25,399 --> 00:16:28,399
And he polymorphed our fighter.

353
00:16:28,399 --> 00:16:30,399
What was his name?

354
00:16:30,399 --> 00:16:32,800
Romaine Broadsword.

355
00:16:32,800 --> 00:16:37,600
Polymorphed him into a T-Rex, just right there.

356
00:16:37,600 --> 00:16:40,800
Should have seen the look on those goblins' faces.

357
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:43,000
So awesome.

358
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:44,800
A T-Rex, you say?

359
00:16:44,800 --> 00:16:46,400
Yeah.

360
00:16:46,400 --> 00:16:48,400
Um...

361
00:16:48,400 --> 00:16:51,400
I have a little question.

362
00:16:51,400 --> 00:16:52,400
Yeah.

363
00:16:52,400 --> 00:16:58,000
Now, we know that Grancis could do some awesome stuff.

364
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:00,000
Of course.

365
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:02,600
And he always had the best intentions.

366
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:04,600
Mm-hmm.

367
00:17:04,600 --> 00:17:06,200
Did...

368
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:11,200
Did Mr. Broadsword ever make it back to his original form?

369
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:12,800
Oh, yeah. Yeah, yeah.

370
00:17:13,799 --> 00:17:17,799
I was wondering the exact same thing.

371
00:17:17,799 --> 00:17:21,799
We met a cool T-Rex, and I thought, it's a pretty small world.

372
00:17:21,799 --> 00:17:25,799
It'd be pretty crazy if that T-Rex I made friends with

373
00:17:25,799 --> 00:17:31,799
was actually Grancis' old friend that he didn't morph back.

374
00:17:31,799 --> 00:17:34,799
No, yeah, I mean, he morphed back pretty soon after that.

375
00:17:34,799 --> 00:17:39,799
I mean, what happened between polymorphings later?

376
00:17:39,799 --> 00:17:43,799
I mean, I suppose anything is possible, but no, no.

377
00:17:43,799 --> 00:17:47,799
Romaine, he turned back, just as you do,

378
00:17:47,799 --> 00:17:50,799
after a polymorph spell, and he...

379
00:17:50,799 --> 00:17:53,799
Yeah, he told that story a lot.

380
00:17:53,799 --> 00:17:55,799
And was it just the three of you,

381
00:17:55,799 --> 00:17:58,799
or was there other adventurers in your group?

382
00:17:58,799 --> 00:18:00,799
No, we had a...

383
00:18:00,799 --> 00:18:03,799
We had a team of eight of us.

384
00:18:03,799 --> 00:18:05,799
Whoa. That's a lot. That's a lot.

385
00:18:05,799 --> 00:18:07,799
Yeah.

386
00:18:07,799 --> 00:18:10,799
You know, strength in numbers, as they say.

387
00:18:10,799 --> 00:18:13,799
But yeah, we had a well-versed crew

388
00:18:13,799 --> 00:18:15,799
who went out a lot of the time.

389
00:18:15,799 --> 00:18:17,799
You guys ever fight a dragon?

390
00:18:17,799 --> 00:18:20,799
Yeah, we fought a dragon before.

391
00:18:20,799 --> 00:18:22,799
Did you win?

392
00:18:22,799 --> 00:18:25,799
Well, we got away.

393
00:18:25,799 --> 00:18:28,799
Hey, nothing's wrong with the win.

394
00:18:28,799 --> 00:18:31,799
Not dying. It's the win in my column.

395
00:18:31,799 --> 00:18:35,799
Yeah, I hear you guys have been going up against some dragons.

396
00:18:35,799 --> 00:18:38,799
Well, obviously we have, because that was yesterday.

397
00:18:38,799 --> 00:18:40,799
Well, yeah.

398
00:18:40,799 --> 00:18:42,799
But others as well.

399
00:18:42,799 --> 00:18:44,799
Thought you might have some hot tips,

400
00:18:44,799 --> 00:18:47,799
some hot dragon-killing tips, but guess not.

401
00:18:47,799 --> 00:18:52,799
Don't use your things that require saving throws.

402
00:18:52,799 --> 00:18:55,799
Or just use lesser things with saving throws

403
00:18:55,799 --> 00:18:58,799
and save your big stuff to the end.

404
00:18:58,799 --> 00:19:00,799
Solid advice.

405
00:19:00,799 --> 00:19:02,799
What's a saving throw, I mean?

406
00:19:02,799 --> 00:19:04,799
I don't know.

407
00:19:05,799 --> 00:19:07,799
A flash of things.

408
00:19:07,799 --> 00:19:09,799
Some divine inspiration.

409
00:19:09,799 --> 00:19:12,799
He says, oh, God, sorry, and fixes her top.

410
00:19:12,799 --> 00:19:14,799
So...

411
00:19:14,799 --> 00:19:17,799
Hasn't been a boob or a dick joke yet.

412
00:19:17,799 --> 00:19:20,799
Yeah, it's true, and we're really far in, so it was good.

413
00:19:20,799 --> 00:19:22,799
He needed to get it.

414
00:19:22,799 --> 00:19:26,799
Thaddeus, how long do you think you're going to stay with us?

415
00:19:26,799 --> 00:19:29,799
Do you have a plan, or are you just going to see how it goes?

416
00:19:29,799 --> 00:19:31,799
No plan.

417
00:19:31,799 --> 00:19:34,799
I mean, I came with you guys to help Grancis with the grungs,

418
00:19:34,799 --> 00:19:38,799
but it seems that, you know,

419
00:19:38,799 --> 00:19:41,799
our path has taken us, brought us together

420
00:19:41,799 --> 00:19:44,799
for what's to come in this dragon,

421
00:19:44,799 --> 00:19:48,799
cult of the dragon battle that we have going on here,

422
00:19:48,799 --> 00:19:53,799
so I'll stick with you until it seems that I should go somewhere else.

423
00:19:53,799 --> 00:19:55,799
What, uh...

424
00:19:55,799 --> 00:19:57,799
Or you have enough with me.

425
00:19:57,799 --> 00:20:00,799
Hey, if we could keep Grancis around for as long as we did.

426
00:20:00,799 --> 00:20:02,799
I think you're all right.

427
00:20:02,799 --> 00:20:05,799
Speaking of Grancis, and you don't have to tell me if you don't want to

428
00:20:05,799 --> 00:20:07,799
because I'm just being snoopy,

429
00:20:07,799 --> 00:20:10,799
but why do you guys have a falling out?

430
00:20:10,799 --> 00:20:12,799
No, it's fine, it's fine.

431
00:20:12,799 --> 00:20:14,799
We, um...

432
00:20:14,799 --> 00:20:18,799
We were on another job.

433
00:20:18,799 --> 00:20:23,799
This was, I don't know, 30 years ago or so.

434
00:20:23,799 --> 00:20:27,799
And...

435
00:20:27,799 --> 00:20:32,799
It wasn't looking good for us.

436
00:20:32,799 --> 00:20:39,799
And Grancis, in his all, in his haste,

437
00:20:39,799 --> 00:20:44,799
miscast a spell, a lightning bolt spell,

438
00:20:44,799 --> 00:20:49,799
and it instead targeted our team

439
00:20:49,799 --> 00:20:55,799
as well as the foes we were fighting.

440
00:20:55,799 --> 00:20:59,799
It was a group of orcs and bugbears,

441
00:20:59,799 --> 00:21:01,799
and they...

442
00:21:01,799 --> 00:21:06,799
I was the only one that survived.

443
00:21:06,799 --> 00:21:10,799
And after that, I just couldn't trust them anymore.

444
00:21:10,799 --> 00:21:13,799
Well, that's reasonable.

445
00:21:13,799 --> 00:21:15,799
That seems...

446
00:21:15,799 --> 00:21:19,799
Well, first of all, terrible, I'm sorry,

447
00:21:19,799 --> 00:21:30,799
but that is certainly a thing to end a friendship over.

448
00:21:30,799 --> 00:21:35,799
But then you decided to help him with the grungs anyway?

449
00:21:35,799 --> 00:21:38,799
I guess it had been a long time, but...

450
00:21:38,799 --> 00:21:43,799
It had been a long time, and I'm a man of faith.

451
00:21:43,799 --> 00:21:48,799
I've been holding back a lot of resentment towards him,

452
00:21:48,799 --> 00:21:52,799
and I didn't want that to hold me back and to hold him back,

453
00:21:52,799 --> 00:21:57,799
because I felt having that possible connection

454
00:21:57,799 --> 00:22:01,799
could have propelled him back into what he could be.

455
00:22:01,799 --> 00:22:03,799
So I took a chance.

456
00:22:03,799 --> 00:22:06,799
He begins to get a little choked up,

457
00:22:06,799 --> 00:22:09,799
and he says,

458
00:22:09,799 --> 00:22:13,799
Well, it's getting late. I'll pack it in here.

459
00:22:13,799 --> 00:22:16,799
You just wake me up when it's my turn for watch.

460
00:22:16,799 --> 00:22:21,799
And he goes to his little tent

461
00:22:21,799 --> 00:22:25,799
and lies down in the bedroll he has laid out there.

462
00:22:25,799 --> 00:22:27,799
What do you guys do?

463
00:22:27,799 --> 00:22:33,799
Probably the same, or else we just decide on watches and go to sleep.

464
00:22:33,799 --> 00:22:36,799
Want to see you guys got any marshmallows?

465
00:22:36,799 --> 00:22:39,799
You want to make some s'mores?

466
00:22:39,799 --> 00:22:43,799
Theo wishes she had marshmallows.

467
00:22:43,799 --> 00:22:45,799
I'll take first watch.

468
00:22:46,799 --> 00:22:48,799
No, you did not.

469
00:22:48,799 --> 00:22:51,799
If I fall asleep now, man, I'm not getting up.

470
00:22:51,799 --> 00:22:55,799
That's true. You're all high and shit still.

471
00:22:55,799 --> 00:22:58,799
All right, I'll take second watch then.

472
00:22:58,799 --> 00:23:03,799
As you guys are determining watches,

473
00:23:03,799 --> 00:23:07,799
some smoke comes off of the fire,

474
00:23:07,799 --> 00:23:11,799
and it kind of hovers there for a minute.

475
00:23:11,799 --> 00:23:14,799
You hear an eerie...

476
00:23:22,799 --> 00:23:26,799
I say, Did anyone else hear that?

477
00:23:26,799 --> 00:23:29,799
I look at my joint and I'm like...

478
00:23:32,799 --> 00:23:35,799
You guys hear that?

479
00:23:35,799 --> 00:23:38,799
How strong is that stuff, Theo?

480
00:23:38,799 --> 00:23:41,799
I feel like it's affecting me.

481
00:23:44,799 --> 00:23:47,799
I don't think it's this.

482
00:23:47,799 --> 00:23:49,799
Grancis?

483
00:23:49,799 --> 00:23:51,799
Oh, you can hear me.

484
00:23:51,799 --> 00:23:53,799
Yeah.

485
00:23:53,799 --> 00:23:55,799
What's up, G-man?

486
00:23:55,799 --> 00:23:59,799
The smoke swirls into not a material form,

487
00:23:59,799 --> 00:24:04,799
but more of a ghostly apparition of Grancis.

488
00:24:04,799 --> 00:24:06,799
He says, Oh, I've been kind of hanging out

489
00:24:06,799 --> 00:24:09,799
following you guys for a little while.

490
00:24:09,799 --> 00:24:12,799
Must have been on ghosts and wind and stuff.

491
00:24:12,799 --> 00:24:15,799
Maybe that just stopped it.

492
00:24:15,799 --> 00:24:20,799
Anyways, thank you for saying all those nice things about me.

493
00:24:20,799 --> 00:24:23,799
The mashed potatoes, they were really good.

494
00:24:23,799 --> 00:24:25,799
You didn't mention the pancakes.

495
00:24:25,799 --> 00:24:28,799
Those pancakes, man, they were legendary.

496
00:24:28,799 --> 00:24:30,799
I was thinking about them.

497
00:24:30,799 --> 00:24:33,799
Yeah, no, it appears.

498
00:24:33,799 --> 00:24:36,799
Ghosts sometimes get locked to things

499
00:24:36,799 --> 00:24:39,799
and then they can't leave.

500
00:24:39,799 --> 00:24:42,799
I'm pretty sure I'm locked to the grungs.

501
00:24:42,799 --> 00:24:44,799
Do you want us to tell Thaddeus

502
00:24:44,799 --> 00:24:48,799
and get him to return them right away?

503
00:24:48,799 --> 00:24:51,799
You think you've got to get them back home?

504
00:24:51,799 --> 00:24:54,799
Don't tell Thaddeus that,

505
00:24:54,799 --> 00:24:56,799
because he'll just want to...

506
00:24:56,799 --> 00:24:58,799
You know, they're good for six months.

507
00:24:58,799 --> 00:25:01,799
I packed them full of seeds and stuff down there

508
00:25:01,799 --> 00:25:03,799
and they should be fine.

509
00:25:03,799 --> 00:25:06,799
I think he really needs to be with you guys.

510
00:25:06,799 --> 00:25:09,799
I'll just kind of hang out.

511
00:25:09,799 --> 00:25:12,799
Grancis, what is the afterlife like?

512
00:25:12,799 --> 00:25:15,799
Right now it's...

513
00:25:15,799 --> 00:25:20,799
There was a bright light.

514
00:25:20,799 --> 00:25:25,799
And then it's hard to keep myself together.

515
00:25:25,799 --> 00:25:27,799
